{"title_page": "Luk\u00e1\u0161 Tich\u00e1\u010dek", "text_new": "{{short description|Czech volleyball player}}\n{{Infobox volleyball biography\n| name           = Luk\u00e1\u0161 Tich\u00e1\u010dek\n| image          = Lukas Tichacek.jpg\n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Luk\u00e1\u0161 Tich\u00e1\u010dek\n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = {{flagicon|CZE}} [[Czech Republic|Czech]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Poland|Polish]]\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1982|1|12|mf=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[P\u0159erov]], [[Czech Republic]]\n| hometown       = \n| height         = {{height|m=1.93|precision=0}}\n| weight         = {{convert|84|kg|lb|abbr=on}}\n| spike          = {{convert|328|cm|abbr=on}}\n| block          = {{convert|324|cm|abbr=on}}\n| college        = \n| position       = Setter\n| currentclub    = {{flagicon|CZE}} VK \u010cEZ Karlovarsko\n| currentnumber  = 5 \n| years          = 2001\u20132006<br>2006\u20132011<br>2011\u20132018<br>2018<br>2018\u20132019<br>2019\u20132020\n| teams          = {{flagicon|CZE}} [[VK Dukla Liberec|Dukla Liberec]]<br> {{flagicon|GER}} [[VfB Friedrichshafen]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Stocznia Szczecin]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[MKS B\u0119dzin]]<br> {{flagicon|CZE}} VK \u010cEZ Karlovarsko\n| nationalyears  = 2003\u2013\n| nationalteam   = {{vb|CZE}}\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry|{{CZE}}}}\n{{MedalSport | Men\u2019s [[Volleyball]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Men's European Volleyball League|European League]]}}\n{{MedalBronze | [[2013 Men's European Volleyball League|2013 Turkey]]|}}\n}}\n\n'''Luk\u00e1\u0161 Tich\u00e1\u010dek''' (born 12 January 1982) is a [[Czech Republic|Czech]] [[volleyball player]] of [[Poland|Polish]] citizenship, a member of [[Czech Republic men's national volleyball team]] and Czech club VK \u010cEZ Karlovarsko, a bronze medalist of the [[2013 Men's European Volleyball League|European League 2013]], two\u2013time Czech Champion (2001, 2003), five\u2013time German Champion (2007, 2008, 2009, 2010, 2011), three\u2013time [[PlusLiga|Polish Champion]] ([[2011\u201312 PlusLiga|2012]], [[2012\u201313 PlusLiga|2013]], [[2014\u201315 PlusLiga|2015]]).\n\n==Personal life==\nIn 2014 he married Paulina. On July 24, 2015 his wife gave birth to their first child, a daughter named Mia.\n\n==Career==\n\n===Clubs===\nOn May 11, 2011 he signed a two-year contract with Polish club [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]].<ref>[http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/4097/title/Tichacek-w-Asseco-Resovii ''Tichacek w Asseco Resovii''] \u2013 plusliga.pl \u2013 11-05-2011</ref> In these two years, he won two titles of Polish Champion (2011/2012,<ref>[http://sport.wp.pl/gid,14431902,kat,1715,title,Asseco-Resovia-mistrzem-Polski,galeria.html?ticaid=113ab0&_ticrsn=5 ''Asseco Resovia mistrzem Polski''] \u2013 sport.wp.pl \u2013 22-04-2012</ref> 2012/2013<ref>[http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/7178/title/Asseco-Resovia-mistrzem-Polski ''Asseco Resovia mistrzem Polski''] \u2013 plusliga.pl \u2013 20-04-2013</ref>). In season 2013/2014 he won Polish SuperCup and silver medal of Polish Championship after losing matches with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]. In 2013, his contract was extended for another two years.<ref>[http://www.sportowefakty.pl/siatkowka/353170/tichacek-zostaje-w-asseco-resovii ''Tichacek zostaje w Asseco Resovii''] \u2013 sportowefakty.pl \u2013 25-04-2013</ref> On March 29, 2015 [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]], including Tichacek, achieved silver medal of the [[2014\u201315 CEV Champions League]].<ref>[http://www.assecoresovia.pl/pl/aktualnosci/wiadomosci/art1992,asseco-resovia-ze-srebrnym-medalem-ligi-mistrzow.html#.VSU2H5Mm-9I ''Asseco Resovia ze srebrnym medalem Ligi Mistrz\u00f3w''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150401013116/http://www.assecoresovia.pl/pl/aktualnosci/wiadomosci/art1992,asseco-resovia-ze-srebrnym-medalem-ligi-mistrzow.html#.VSU2H5Mm-9I |date=2015-04-01 }} \u2013 assecoresovia.pl \u2013 29-03-2015</ref><ref>[http://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/CompetitionNews.aspx?ID=736&NewsID=19956&TagType=0&TagContent=0&NewsType=0&Paging=0&Sd=1/1/1900&Ed=1/1/1900 ''Three is the magic number for Russian armada from Tatarstan! ''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210181047/http://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/CompetitionNews.aspx?ID=736&NewsID=19956&TagType=0&TagContent=0&NewsType=0&Paging=0&Sd=1%2F1%2F1900&Ed=1%2F1%2F1900 |date=2018-02-10 }} \u2013 cev.eu \u2013 29-03-2015</ref> In April 2015 he signed next two-year contract till 2017.<ref>[http://www.assecoresovia.pl/pl/aktualnosci/wiadomosci/art2010,lukas-tichacek-w-asseco-resovii-na-kolejne-dwa-lata.html#.VSU1PJMm-9I ''Lukas Tichacek w Asseco Resovii na kolejne dwa lata!''] \u2013 assecoresovia.pl \u2013 07-04-2015</ref>\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''[[CEV Champions League]]'''\n** [[File:Gold medal europe.svg|16px]] [[Men's CEV Champions League 2006\u201307|2006/2007]] \u2013 with [[VfB Friedrichshafen]]\n** [[File:Silver medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2014\u201315 CEV Champions League|2014/2015]] \u2013 with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n\n* '''[[CEV Cup]]'''\n** [[File:Simple bronze cup.svg|16px]] 2004/2005 \u2013 with [[VK Dukla Liberec|Dukla Liberec]]\n** [[File:Simple silver cup.svg|16px]] [[2011\u201312 Men's CEV Cup|2011/2012]] \u2013 with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n\n* '''National championships'''\n** '''2000/2001''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Czech Cup, with [[VK Dukla Liberec|Dukla Liberec]]\n** '''2000/2001''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Czech Championship, with [[VK Dukla Liberec|Dukla Liberec]]\n** '''2002/2003''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Czech Championship, with [[VK Dukla Liberec|Dukla Liberec]]\n** '''2003/2004''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] Czech Championship, with [[VK Dukla Liberec|Dukla Liberec]]\n** '''2004/2005''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] Czech Championship, with [[VK Dukla Liberec|Dukla Liberec]]\n** '''2005/2006''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] Czech Championship, with [[VK Dukla Liberec|Dukla Liberec]]\n** '''2006/2007''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] German Cup, with [[VfB Friedrichshafen]]\n** '''2006/2007''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] German Championship, with [[VfB Friedrichshafen]]\n** '''2007/2008''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] German Cup, with [[VfB Friedrichshafen]]\n** '''2007/2008''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] German Championship, with [[VfB Friedrichshafen]]\n** '''2008/2009''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] German Championship, with [[VfB Friedrichshafen]]\n** '''2009/2010''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] German Championship, with [[VfB Friedrichshafen]]\n** '''2010/2011''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] German Championship, with [[VfB Friedrichshafen]]\n** '''2011/2012''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2011\u201312 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n** '''2012/2013''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2012\u201313 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n** '''2013/2014''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish SuperCup, with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n** '''2013/2014''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2013\u201314 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n** '''2014/2015''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2014\u201315 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n** '''2015/2016''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2015\u201316 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n\n* '''National team'''\n** '''2013''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2013 Men's European Volleyball League|European League]]\n\n===Individually===\n* '''2010:''' [[Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner]] \u2013 Best Setter\n* '''2011:''' [[Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner]] \u2013 Best Setter\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.plusliga.pl/players/id/420 PlusLiga Player profile]\n\n{{commons}}\n{{Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w team}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tichacek, Lukas}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from P\u0159erov]]\n[[Category:German men's volleyball players]]\n[[Category:Czech men's volleyball players]]\n[[Category:Czech expatriates in Germany]]\n[[Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Germany]]\n[[Category:Czech expatriates in Poland]]\n[[Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Poland]]\n[[Category:Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Czech volleyball player}}\n{{Infobox volleyball biography\n| name           = Luk\u00e1\u0161 Tich\u00e1\u010dek\n| image          = Lukas Tichacek.jpg\n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Luk\u00e1\u0161 Tich\u00e1\u010dek\n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = {{flagicon|CZE}} [[Czech Republic|Czech]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Poland|Polish]]\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1982|1|12|mf=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[P\u0159erov]], [[Czech Republic]]\n| hometown       = \n| height         = {{height|m=1.93|precision=0}}\n| weight         = {{convert|84|kg|lb|abbr=on}}\n| spike          = {{convert|328|cm|abbr=on}}\n| block          = {{convert|324|cm|abbr=on}}\n| college        = \n| position       = Setter\n| currentclub    = {{flagicon|CZE}} VK \u010cEZ Karlovarsko\n| currentnumber  = 5 \n| years          = 2001\u20132006<br>2006\u20132011<br>2011\u20132018<br>2018<br>2018\u20132019<br>2019\u20132020\n| teams          = {{flagicon|CZE}} [[VK Dukla Liberec|Dukla Liberec]]<br> {{flagicon|GER}} [[VfB Friedrichshafen]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Stocznia Szczecin]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[MKS B\u0119dzin]]<br> {{flagicon|CZE}} VK \u010cEZ Karlovarsko\n| nationalyears  = 2003\u2013\n| nationalteam   = {{vb|CZE}}\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry|{{CZE}}}}\n{{MedalSport | Men\u2019s [[Volleyball]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Men's European Volleyball League|European League]]}}\n{{MedalBronze | [[2013 Men's European Volleyball League|2013 Turkey]]|}}\n}}\n\n'''Luk\u00e1\u0161 Tich\u00e1\u010dek''' (born 12 January 1982) is a [[Czech Republic|Czech]] [[volleyball player]] of [[Poland|Polish]] citizenship, a member of [[Czech Republic men's national volleyball team]] and Czech club VK \u010cEZ Karlovarsko, a bronze medalist of the [[2013 Men's European Volleyball League|European League 2013]], two\u2013time Czech Champion (2001, 2003), five\u2013time German Champion (2007, 2008, 2009, 2010, 2011), three\u2013time [[PlusLiga|Polish Champion]] ([[2011\u201312 PlusLiga|2012]], [[2012\u201313 PlusLiga|2013]], [[2014\u201315 PlusLiga|2015]]).\n\n==Personal life==\nIn 2014 he married Paulina. On July 24, 2015 his wife gave birth to their first child, a daughter named Mia.\n\n==Career==\n\n===Clubs===\nOn May 11, 2011 he signed a two-year contract with Polish club [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]].<ref>[http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/4097/title/Tichacek-w-Asseco-Resovii ''Tichacek w Asseco Resovii''] \u2013 plusliga.pl \u2013 11-05-2011</ref> In these two years, he won two titles of Polish Champion (2011/2012,<ref>[http://sport.wp.pl/gid,14431902,kat,1715,title,Asseco-Resovia-mistrzem-Polski,galeria.html?ticaid=113ab0&_ticrsn=5 ''Asseco Resovia mistrzem Polski''] \u2013 sport.wp.pl \u2013 22-04-2012</ref> 2012/2013<ref>[http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/7178/title/Asseco-Resovia-mistrzem-Polski ''Asseco Resovia mistrzem Polski''] \u2013 plusliga.pl \u2013 20-04-2013</ref>). In season 2013/2014 he won Polish SuperCup and silver medal of Polish Championship after losing matches with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]. In 2013, his contract was extended for another two years.<ref>[http://www.sportowefakty.pl/siatkowka/353170/tichacek-zostaje-w-asseco-resovii ''Tichacek zostaje w Asseco Resovii''] \u2013 sportowefakty.pl \u2013 25-04-2013</ref> On March 29, 2015 [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]], including Tichacek, achieved silver medal of the [[2014\u201315 CEV Champions League]].<ref>[http://www.assecoresovia.pl/pl/aktualnosci/wiadomosci/art1992,asseco-resovia-ze-srebrnym-medalem-ligi-mistrzow.html#.VSU2H5Mm-9I ''Asseco Resovia ze srebrnym medalem Ligi Mistrz\u00f3w''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150401013116/http://www.assecoresovia.pl/pl/aktualnosci/wiadomosci/art1992,asseco-resovia-ze-srebrnym-medalem-ligi-mistrzow.html#.VSU2H5Mm-9I |date=2015-04-01 }} \u2013 assecoresovia.pl \u2013 29-03-2015</ref><ref>[http://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/CompetitionNews.aspx?ID=736&NewsID=19956&TagType=0&TagContent=0&NewsType=0&Paging=0&Sd=1/1/1900&Ed=1/1/1900 ''Three is the magic number for Russian armada from Tatarstan! ''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210181047/http://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/CompetitionNews.aspx?ID=736&NewsID=19956&TagType=0&TagContent=0&NewsType=0&Paging=0&Sd=1%2F1%2F1900&Ed=1%2F1%2F1900 |date=2018-02-10 }} \u2013 cev.eu \u2013 29-03-2015</ref> In April 2015 he signed next two-year contract till 2017.<ref>[http://www.assecoresovia.pl/pl/aktualnosci/wiadomosci/art2010,lukas-tichacek-w-asseco-resovii-na-kolejne-dwa-lata.html#.VSU1PJMm-9I ''Lukas Tichacek w Asseco Resovii na kolejne dwa lata!''] \u2013 assecoresovia.pl \u2013 07-04-2015</ref>\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''[[CEV Champions League]]'''\n** [[File:Gold medal europe.svg|16px]] [[Men's CEV Champions League 2006\u201307|2006/2007]] \u2013 with [[VfB Friedrichshafen]]\n** [[File:Silver medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2014\u201315 CEV Champions League|2014/2015]] \u2013 with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n\n* '''[[CEV Cup]]'''\n** [[File:Simple bronze cup.svg|16px]] 2004/2005 \u2013 with [[VK Dukla Liberec|Dukla Liberec]]\n** [[File:Simple silver cup.svg|16px]] [[2011\u201312 Men's CEV Cup|2011/2012]] \u2013 with [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n\n* '''National championships'''\n** '''2000/2001''' [[