The [[1998 Melanesia Cup]] and the [[1998 Polynesia Cup]] were used to find the four qualifiers for the finals tournament ([[Fiji national football team|Fiji]] and [[Vanuatu national football team|Vanuatu]] from Melanesia and [[Tahiti national football team|Tahiti]] and [[Cook Islands national football team|Cook Islands]] from Polynesia respectively), to move on and join [[Australia national football team|Australia]] and [[New Zealand national football team|New Zealand]] at the main tournament.\n\nPlayers marked ([[Captain (association football)|c]]) were named as captain for their national squad. Players' club teams and players' age are as of 25 September 1998 \u2013 the tournament's opening day.\n\n==Squad lists==\n===Australia===\nCoach: {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Raul Blanco]]\n{{nat fs start}}\n{{nat fs player|no=1|pos=GK|name=[[Jason Petkovic]]|age={{Birth date and age2|1998|9|25|1972|12|7|df=y}}|caps=|club=[[Adelaide City FC|Adelaide City]]|clubnat=AUS}}\n{{nat fs player|no=2|pos=DF|name=[[Robert Trajkovski]]|age={{Birth date and age2|1998|9|25|1972|7|24|df=y}}|caps=|club=[[Perth Glory FC|Perth Glory]]|clubnat=AUS}}\n{{nat fs player|no=3|pos=DF|name=[[Fausto De Amicis]]|age={{Birth date and age2|1998|9|25|1968|6|26|df=y}}|caps=|club=[[South Melbourne FC|South Melbourne]]|clubnat=AUS}}\n{{nat fs player|no=4|pos=DF|name=[[Glenn Gwynne]]|age={{Birth date and age2|1998|9|25|1972|2|22|df=y}}|caps=|club=[[Brisbane Strikers FC|Brisbane Strikers]]|clubnat=AUS}}\n{{nat fs player|no=5|pos=DF|name=[[Alex Tobin]] ([[Captain (association football)|c]])|age={{Birth date and age2|1998|9|25|1965|11|3|df=y}}|caps=|club=[[Adelaide City FC|Adelaide City]]|clubnat=AUS}}\n{{nat fs player|no=6|pos=DF|name=[[Mark Babic]]|age={{Birth date and age2|1998|9|25|1973|4|24|df=y}}|caps=|club=[[Marconi Stallions FC|Marconi Stallions]]|clubnat=AUS}}\n{{nat fs player|no=7|pos=MF|name=[[Ernie Tapai]]|age={{Birth date and age2|1998|9|25|1967|2|14|df=y}}|caps=|club=[[Perth Glory FC|Perth Glory]]|clubnat