 Edward Petrovitch made the announcement Tuesday evening, March 17, 2020, during a special meeting of the Board of Supervisors.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327030727/https://spotsylvania.va.us/CivicAlerts.aspx?AID=162|archive-date=March 27, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Clarke County, Virginia|Clarke County]] Board of Supervisors adopted a declaration of local emergency.<ref>{{cite web|first=Mickey|last=Powell|date=March 18, 2020|url=https://www.winchesterstar.com/coronavirus/coronavirus-prompts-clarke-county-to-declare-emergency/article_f448b813-29a0-569d-9a9f-f7945d63fd71.html|title=Coronavirus prompts Clarke County to declare emergency|location=[[Winchester, Virginia]]|publisher=[[The Winchester Star]]|accessdate=March 29, 2020|quote=A local emergency declaration was adopted by the Clarke County Board of Supervisors in a unanimous vote Tuesday afternoon. .... The declaration also enables the county, if it eventually becomes necessary, to \u201ccontrol, restrict, allocate or regulate the use, sale, production or distribution of food, fuel, clothing and other commodities, materials, goods, services and resource systems which fall only within the boundaries\u201d of Clarke County and do not affect nearby localities.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318133347/https://www.winchesterstar.com/coronavirus/coronavirus-prompts-clarke-county-to-declare-emergency/article_f448b813-29a0-569d-9a9f-f7945d63fd71.html|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Culpeper County, Virginia|Culpeper County]] Board of Supervisors declared a local state of emergency.<ref>(1) {{cite news|url=https://www.starexponent.com/news/culpeper-county-declares-local-state-of-emergency/article_ac4692c4-133b-5fbd-9943-6239093d332f.html|title=Culpeper County declares local state of emergency|date=March 17, 2020|location=[[Culpeper, Virginia]]|publisher=Culpeper Star-Exponent|accessdate=March 29, 2020}}<br>(2) {{cite news|first=Pat|last=Fitzgerald|date=Ma